{
  "text": "We have been investigating the impact of a bipolar ablation to treat VTs with a septal substrate, approached with two ablation catheters opposing each other across the septum to create a transmural lesion (Figure 7 ). [CITATION_1] For intramural lesion, irrigated needle ablations might be of future help. [CITATION_2] ",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "32001123",
